Descriptions: The name of the Profile that will appear to your users. Longer names may be truncated on small devices, so consider short names.
The numeric value that overrides the default alphanumeric order of Profile Groups. Profile Groups with blanks will be sorted alphanumerically and displayed below Profile Groups with numbers.
The description of the Profile that will appear to your users. User longer descriptions in conjunction with shorter names to accommodate small screen formats.
The name of the Profile Group that this Profile belongs to.
Controls whether users can modify this Profile. A locked Profile is considered read-only and cannot be modified.
Boolean value to set the Show (visibility) of the Profile. A setting of False will suppress the display of the Profile to users.
Boolean value to get whether or not the Profile is the default Profile. You can have only 1 default Profile, which will be displayed to a user who has not selected a Profile.
List of Active Directory or local groups (semicolon separated) defining access rights to the object. Only applies if Object Level Security is enabled and the site is secured.
